* ff+4,2, qcf+1, f+3 hits, but sometimes you can get a dash d+3 -&amp;gt; qcb+1 for TS!&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
== Character Specific Notes ==&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
=== Josie ===&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
* In combos after TS! fff+3, the b+4 won't connect. You'll have to switch it to d+3&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
=== Jack ===&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
* d+1 -4 qcb+4 hits him too high for the CH d+1 -&amp;gt; qcb+4, 1 -&amp;gt; f,d,df+2 doesn't combo.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
== Things to try ==&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
* can grounded 1+2 (sleep stance transition) avoid some ground hitting moves?&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
* How consistent is b+1,2,4 on hitting side rolling opponents in the open? How about at the wall?&lt;br /&gt;
* Combo: W! uf~qcb+3, d+1 -&amp;gt; f,d,df1 W! -&amp;gt; stuff (like in here: https://youtu.be/r4mx5ETdiNw?t=202)&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
