== Wall Combos ==&lt;br /&gt;
Max damage without peel off: W! 2, df+1,2,f+1+2&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Great for Oki and continued wall pressure: W! df+3,2, 1+4 - This puts them in the flop animation. If they don't hold b then qcf+2, db+3, WTF will all hit them and provide good mixup material if they do hold b&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
If you get a heavy wall stun (ie: f+3 -&amp;gt; W! or uf+3 -&amp;gt; W!) you can do a quick back dash, SSR+1~b~u, ss+1~b~u~f+1,2,f+1+2&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
If you need a wall break or balcony break you can do:&lt;br /&gt;
W! df+3,2, b+1+2 or W! df+1, b+1+2 for a safer option&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
After a balcony break - if you're many hits into the combo, you don't get much... usually just a f,F+1+2. If you're still in the early hits you can db+2 or f+3 for TS and continue the combo from there.&lt;br /&gt;
